---
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import Cta from "@components/cta.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "@components/navbar/navbar.astro";
import Reviews from "@components/reviews.astro";
import Contactbtn from "@components/contactbtn.astro";
import Btn from "@components/btn.astro";
import { Accordion, AccordionItem,Icon } from 'free-astro-components'

import "css/brands/style-brands.css";

const description = "Expert LG freezer repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, and Ventura County. Same Day Appliance Repair provides same-day service, OEM parts, and a 90-day warranty.";
const title = "Same Day LG Freezer Repair LA | Same Day Service";
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <head>
    <script type="application/ld+json" is:raw>
      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "Service",
        "serviceType": "LG Freezer Repair",
        "provider": {
          "@type": "Organization",
          "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair",
          "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/",
          "logo": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair-logo.webp",
          "telephone": "+13238704790",
          "email": "info@samedayappliance.repair",
          "areaServed": [
            { "@type": "Place", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
            { "@type": "Place", "name": "Orange County" },
            { "@type": "Place", "name": "Ventura County" }
          ]
        },
        "description": "Same Day Appliance Repair provides expert LG freezer repair services with OEM parts and same-day availability across Los Angeles, Orange County, and Ventura County.",
        "mainEntityOfPage": "https://samedayappliance.repair/lg-freezer-repair-los-angeles/"
      }
    </script>
  </head>
<Navbar />
<Reviews />
 
  <Container>
    <div class="full-page">
      <div class="page-header">
        <span class="animate-charcter">
          <h1 style="color: #fff !important;">Same Day LG Freezer Repair in Los Angeles</h1>
          </span>
        <h3>Factory Trained • Fast Service • OEM Parts Guaranteed</h3>

        <h2>Expert LG Freezer Repair Across Southern California</h2>
        
        <p>If your <strong>LG freezer</strong> isn't staying cold, is leaking, making buzzing or clicking noises, or displaying temperature errors, don't wait—especially with high summer temps. At <strong>Same Day Appliance Repair</strong>, we specialize in <strong>LG freezer repair and service</strong> for frost-free, under-counter, chest, and garage-ready models. Using genuine LG OEM parts, factory service guides, and years of specialized experience, we understand the unique engineering of LG's cooling systems—and we fix issues correctly the first time. High-quality LG units still require expert care and routine maintenance to prevent food loss and costly breakdowns.</p>
        
        <p>With dual hubs covering <strong>Los Angeles, Orange County, and Ventura County</strong> , we offer <strong>same-day freezer repair</strong>, transparent pricing, and a <strong>90-day parts and labor warranty</strong> on every job.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Related Service:</strong>
            For matching Whirlpool fridge repairs, visit our 
            <a href="/services/refrigerator-repair-los-angeles/" 
                  class="underline font-bold" 
                  style="color: #dc2626 !important;">
                  Refrigerator Repair Los Angeles
               </a>
             page.
            </p>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-2">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Types of LG Freezers We Repair</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="right-content">
            <p>Our technicians fix all residential LG freezer styles and sub-brands, including:</p>
            <ul>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Frost-free upright models</strong> (e.g., LMXS28626S, LRFCS28968)</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Compact under-counter or apartment-sized units</strong> (e.g., LCUC1451ST, LFC24770ST)</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Manual-defrost chest freezers</strong>—popular for garages and workshops</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Combo fridge/freezer or side-by-side units</strong> (e.g., LSXS26326S), all backed by LG's Dual Evaporator or Door Cooling+ systems</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top: 20px;">Whether it's a side-by-side refrigerator-freezer or a standalone chest model, our techs carry specialized part catalogs tailored to each type.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-3">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Common LG Freezer Problems We Fix</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <p>Locating and repairing LG freezer failures is our specialty. Here's what we fix most often:</p>
            <ul>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Inconsistent Cooling or Warming Food</strong> — Often caused by dirty condenser coils, frost-clogged evaporator fins, failed defrost heater, or blocked airflow—leading a freeze compartment to struggle while the fridge remains cold.</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Freezer Runs Continuously Without Freezing</strong> — If your LG freezer runs but never reaches 0 °F, it may be a bad main control board or a locked compressor that can't build pressure.</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Clicking or Buzzing Sounds</strong> — Rapid clicks often mean a faulty start relay or compressor attempting a startup and failing repeatedly.</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Thick Frost or Ice Build-Up</strong> — Ice on evaporator plates or lining freezer walls usually signals failed defrost cycles or gasket leaks.</li>
              <li class="flex items-center gap-2" ><Icon icon="check" class="icon-class" /><strong>Ice-Maker Overflows or Provider Leaks</strong> — Inlets sticking or frozen fill tubes cause leaks in upright models—common in side-by-side and family hub designs.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-4">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Genuine LG Parts We Stock for Fast Fixes</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <p>We keep these OEM LG parts in service vans so most jobs finish on the first visit:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">
                <span><strong>Evaporator fan motor / duct assembly</strong> (LG EAU61524007 or EAU62064602) – crucial for airflow and even cooling.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">
                <span><strong>Control board / PCB assembly</strong> (EBR81182789, EBR30299301, EBR80757402) – manages defrost timing, compressor cycles, and control panel interface.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">
                <span><strong>Start relay and overload kit</strong> – essential for reliable compressor starts</span>
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">
                <span><strong>Defrost heater kit & sensor</strong> – restores proper frost cycles and prevents ice buildup</span>
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">
                <span><strong>Door gasket sets</strong> – official LG seals for thermally-tight doors and frost prevention</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top: 20px;">These factory parts offer better fit, reliability, and warranty coverage compared to aftermarket alternatives.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-5">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Repair or Replace? Our Honest Assessment</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <p>If your LG freezer is under 10 years old, hasn't lost refrigerant, and shows no sealed-system issues, repair is likely the most cost-effective option. We at Same Day Appliance Repair evaluate age, visible condition, refrigerant integrity, and labor cost to provide you a straightforward recommendation—no upsells, just transparent options.
            </p>

            <h3>Typical LG Freezer Repair Costs</h3>
            <p>Every LG freezer quote includes:</p>

            <ul class="space-y-4">
                <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">Flat diagnostic fee (credited upon repair approval)</li>
                <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">OEM part costs and labor by EPA-licensed technicians</li>
                <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">Insurance, licensing & tech certifications</li>
                <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2"><strong>90-day parts & labor warranty</strong></li>
                <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913] flex items-center gap-2">10% discount on your next repair</li>
              </ul>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-top: 20px;">For benchmark pricing, see our detailed <a href="/price-list/freezer-repair-cost/" class="underline font-bold" style="color: #dc2626 !important;">Freezer Repair Cost Guide</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-6">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>How Our LG Freezer Service Works</h2>
          </div>

          <p style="margin-top: 10px;">Our process stays the same no matter the brand:</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <ul class="space-y-4">
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                Book online or by phone before 3 PM for same-day service
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                Receive ETA and technician profile by text
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                On-site inspection, explained in plain English
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                You approve the quote—deposit collected
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                Parts installed (most are pre-stocked)
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                Repair performed, then tested and finalized
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                Digital invoice, warranty & care tips emailed
              </li>
              <li class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border-l-4 border-[#ca0913]">
                10% return-customer discount and lifetime support
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-7">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Other Brands We Service</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <p style="margin-top: 20px;">In addition to LG, we repair appliances from <strong>Whirlpool, GE, Frigidaire, Maytag, Samsung, Sub-Zero, Thermador, and others.</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      
      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-8">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) – LG Freezer Repair</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
            <div class="full-width-content">
            <Accordion variant='splitted' title="LG Freezer Repair FAQ">
              <AccordionItem title="Why is my LG freezer section warm while the fridge stays cold?">
                <p>This usually points to airflow issues (like a failed evaporator fan or frost buildup) or defrost system failure in the freezer.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="My LG freezer clicks but won't freeze—what should I check?">
                <p>Clicking often means the compressor start relay is faulty or the compressor is struggling to start under load. Our techs test and pinpoint the right solution.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="Ice is piling up at the back wall—what's the likely problem?">
                <p>That indicates a failing defrost system or a gasket leak, which lets ambient air in and freezes. Prompt service typically stops frost buildup.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="My ice bucket keeps flooding—is there a fix?">
                <p>Yes. A blocked or frozen inlet fill tube or stuck valve usually causes overflow. Replacing the valve normally stops the leak.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
              
              <AccordionItem title="The freezer is dead—no light, no cooling—what now?">
                <p>First check power, control panel and breakers. If it's fully cold, a failed main control board (e.g., LG EBR80757402) might be the culprit.</p>
              </AccordionItem>
            </Accordion>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-9">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>Call Now – Schedule Your LG Freezer Repair</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <p style="margin-top: 20px;">Whether you're in <strong>Los Angeles, Pasadena, Glendale, Santa Monica, Burbank, Irvine, Long Beach, Anaheim, or Thousand Oaks</strong>, our local LG freezer experts are available today. We'll get your freezer back to 0 °F so your food stays safe.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="page-container" id="anchor-10">
        <div class="header-container">
          <div class="head-content-h">
            <h2>About Same Day Appliance Repair</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-container">
          <div class="full-width-content">
            <p>Same Day Appliance Repair is Southern California's <strong>BBB-accredited, A+ rated appliance service team</strong>. Our licensed, insured, and factory-trained technicians repair <strong>LG, GE, Frigidaire, Whirlpool, and more</strong>—using only OEM parts and owner-approved repair manuals. Every job comes with transparent pricing, same-day arrival, and our 90-day parts and labor guarantee.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top: 15px;">Book online now at <a href="/" class="underline font-bold " style="color: #dc2626 !important;"> samedayappliance.repair </a> or call <strong>(323) 870‑4790</strong> to schedule your LG freezer repair today.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="contact-section">
        <Contactbtn />
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
 
